	<a name="basic"></a>
	<h2 class="mb10">Basic Rules</h2>
	Please read the following rules and guidelines very carefully. By proceeding to post you agree to these rules and must obey them at all times. Refusal to obey these rules will result in the appropriate responsive actions by the moderation team. Please note that LB reserves the right to revise and alter these rules, guidelines and policies at any time, without warning.
	<br />
	<br />
	We have implemented the following guide for using our community forums. This guide is designed to strike a balance between the main goal of our forums, providing support, and keeping the relaxed and welcoming atmosphere for the user community.
	<br />
	<br />
	We require all posts to be polite, constructive, and on topic.
	<br />
	<br />
	All material posted or uploaded to the forum remains the property of the original poster and Media Panther Ltd is the licensed distributor of such content. The administrators of this site reserve the right without notice to access or view all such material (including posts, profile information, emails sent through the forum software, and Personal Messages (PMs)), to edit the subject of a post, or to move, reclassify, or delete any post or other material that is deemed inappropriate or disruptive, fails to conform to these forum rules, or to ensure proper indexing and searchability. Please note that, from time to time, topics may be removed for being inappropriate even though your individual post in that topic may have been perfectly fine. Please do not feel this reflects badly on you.
	<br />
	<br />
	Having fun is good. We like fun. Please keep it positive and polite. We may take action against posts and/or topics that could cause unrest in the community beyond a civil and polite disagreement.
	<br />
	<br />
	You may not make personal attacks on other users or staff members, either in public forums or private messages.
	<br />
	<br />
	You may not use overly gross profanity. Many visitors access the site from professional places, such as offices, and this risks the visitor getting into trouble, or embarrassed. We have word filters in place for the most vulgar terms. Circumventing those word filters will result in punitive action.
	<br />
	<br />
	We reserve the right to ban any member who violates our guidelines or disrupts our community. We will be fair and provide ample warning in most cases.
	<br />
	<br />
	If you have an issue concerning our services, policies, or staff, please use a personal contact method such as a private message or email to a staff member. The staff and moderators are listed <a href="../">here</a>. We take serious complaints to heart and will do our best to address them.
	<br />
	<br />
	<br />
	<a name="forum"></a>
	<h2 class="mb10">The Forum Rules</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>There will be no racial, ethnic, gender based insults or any other personal discriminations.<br /><br /></li>
		<li>There will be no posts meant to offend or hurt any other member, in a manner which is offensive or inflammatory.<br /><br /></li>
		<li>Spamming is not permitted; please keep all your posts as constructive as possible.<br /><br /></li>
		<li>Pornography, warez, or any other illegal transactions may NOT be linked or attached in any shape or form. This includes avatars.<br /><br /></li>
		<li>Users may not argue a moderators decision publicly. Any and all complaints directed at a moderator must first address the moderator in question via PM. If the problem can not be resolved, then the moderator and user must send their positions to the forum admin. The forum admin will make or change any and/or all final decisions.<br /><br /></li>
		<li>Pictures may be posted as long as they are not explicit or offensive. You must be the copyright holder to upload a picture, though linking to copyrighted material is acceptable. Common courtesy is to also provide a link to the supporting page/site.<br /><br /></li>
		<li>Signatures may contain images, but may not be any larger than 468 x 60 pixels. If your signature is larger than the allotted size given or deemed unacceptable by staff, you will be requested by a moderator to resize or change your image. Please also try and keep text signatures under 5 lines. Failing to comply with a moderator's request will result in the removal of your signature.<br /><br /></li>
		<li>Commercial promotion by business' is strictly prohibited unless you are a paid site sponsor. Commercial prmotion can be described as, but not limited to advertising, solicitation, recommendations or links in signatures. Site sponsorship is discussed on our <a href="/advertising/">advertising page</a>. Site sponsorship is extremely cost-effective, supports the site and allows business' to promote themselves within the forums.<br /><br /></li>
		<li>Remember to post in the correct forum. Take your time to look at other topics and see where your topic should go. If your topic is placed in the wrong forum, it will be moved by a moderator.<br /><br /></li>
		<li>If a topic is recognised as being posted in the wrong forum, or if the post is a violation of our guidelines then please contact a moderator via PM; please do not respond publicly to the member - a member of staff will do what is required upon contact. Any person/s who attempt to present themselves as a Moderator by posting negatively to a member's topic (which has been posted in error and requires locking or moving to another forum) will be sent a PM warning.<br /><br /></li>
		<li>Any impersonation of a user within these forums, in any mode of communication, is strictly prohibited and will result in a banning. This includes gaining access to another members account.<br /><br /></li>
		<li>Linked and locked topics may be pruned regularly to reduce page clutter. If you have a question about where your topic went, please PM a Moderator or Administrator before starting a new topic asking where it went, or posting a duplicate of the original topic. We will be happy to provide you with a link to the new location, or a reason why it was locked and/or removed.<br /><br /></li>
		<li>If you are linking to external content, you should link directly to that content. It is unacceptable to use link-through systems to mask the originating URL, and cases where this is found to be happening may be edited or removed as appropriate.<br /><br /></li>
		<li>If you are hot-linking (showing from another site) images or other content from another site, its good manners to provide a link to the site as well, so that viewers can see where it came from. This is a courtesy for the remote site’s administrators.</li>
	</ol>
	<br />
	Violation of any of these rules will result in consequences determined on a case-by-case basis, by the moderation team.
