	<a name="explanations"></a>
	<h2 class="mb10">Explanations</h2>
	<b>Purpose</b>
	<br />
	The purpose of the forums is to discuss ALL topics of biking. The LB forums are here to offer a structured and open place to discuss anything biking related, and a space is also provided to discuss off-topic subjects.
	<br />
	<br />
	We reserve the right to stop excessively long and unproductive threads.
	<br />
	<br />
	<b>Acceptable Topics</b>
	<br />
	Nothing relating to biking is off topic for the LB forums.
	<br />
	<br />
	Humor is encouraged. Goodness knows we can all use a little bit now and then. The use of emoticons is also encouraged; they go a long way towards expressing the mood of your post and getting your point across. :o)
	<br />
	<br />
	<b>Off Topics</b>
	<br />
	If you feel you have a post that is off topic but may be of use to the community, please post it in the General Chatter forums, which is off-topic friendly.
	<br />
	<br />
	<b>Misunderstandings</b>
	<br />
	LB has members from all around the world, which brings together a collection of individuals with different personalities and different ways of communicating ideas. In the electronic medium, it is easy to misinterpret a comment as sarcastic or offensive, when no such message was intended by the original sender. Please keep this in mind when reading and responding to posts.
	<br />
	<br />
	<b>Flaming and Rough Mannerisms</b>
	<br />
	No Flames: The posting of any material that defames, maligns, slanders, or is uncivil to any other individual or group is strictly prohibited. Please keep the tone of posts respectful of others. 
	<br />
	<br />
	Let us be clear. Flaming and/or harassing behavior will NOT be tolerated. Posts shall not request harassing, abusive, aggressive, or hostile actions to be taken against another individual or group, whether a member of LB or not. Do not respond to flames directly on the site.
	<br />
	<br />
	Furthermore, the defaming of other discussion communities will not be tolerated.
	<br />
	<br />
	Repetitive violations of rules and/or flames with foul language or subject matter inappropriate for the LB forums will result in penalties being placed by the moderation team.
	<br />
	<br />
	Provoking another member of LB into a confrontation is grounds for REVIEW by the moderation team.
	<br />
	<br />
	In the event that your actions are reviewed due to rough mannerisms you will be given an opportunity to explain the situation. If we find that you were simply misunderstood, no action will be taken against you. An apology to the other member may be required.
	<br />
	<br />
	<b>Unacceptable Material</b>
	<br />
	Including the following in your postings is considered unacceptable by LB:
	<br />
	<ul>
		<li><i>Copyrighted material</i><br />The redistribution or posting of copyrighted material without written permission from the copyright holder is strictly prohibited and can result in the immediate suspension or removal from LB. This includes any material posted from another website or person. This also includes all forwarded e-mail.<br /><br /></li>
		<li><i>Advertising and Spamming:</i><br />Advertising of any kind is not allowed by LB, unless given prior consent by the forum administrators. You may submit your site URL for critique, or suggest it as a place to find help for a particular topic being discussed. But blatant plugs, advertising, or spamming of any kind will result in the offenders immediate removal from LB.<br /><br /></li>
		<li><i>Solicitation:</i><br />
			This is considered the same as Advertising and Spamming. The discussion of prices for products and certain services is acceptable. Advertising your rates for the purpose of business solicitation is not allowed on the LB forums, without permission of the forum administrators.</li><br />
			A list of subjects that fall under this heading are:<br />
			o	Products or services you are selling or are considering selling<br />
			o	Website advertising rates ("banner ads", etc.)<br /><br /></li>
		<li><i>Foul language and inappropriate material:</i><br />
			Keep in mind that members may view the site from locations that require a professional outlook, such as offices. Please refrain from cussing or using any other foul language. Also, refrain from discussing material that would be considered inappropriate for minors.</li>
	</ul>
	<br />
	<a name="issues"></a>
	<h2 class="mb10">Issue Procedure</h2>
	The LB moderation team are there to ensure the balance is kept in the forums, as part of this, there may be times when a member breaks the forum rules and comes under inspection of a moderator. A moderator will do everything they can to settle any breach of the rules, or dispute, as fairly as possible.
	<br />
	<br />
	To prevent any unfair treatment of a member who has broken the forum rules, a three-strike penalty system is in place to ensure that the member gets a second chance to continue their membership with LB.
	<br />
	<ul>
		<li><i>Strike 1 – Yellow Card</i><br />
			You are given a formal warning by a moderator and given a chance to redeem yourself. This will remain active for three months.<br /><br /></li>
		<li><i>Strike 2 – Red Card</i><br />
			If you offend again under a yellow card, of if the offence is serious enough, you will be suspended for a period of one month. After this period, the red card will remain on record for 12 months.<br /><br /></li>
		<li><i>Strike 3 – Black Card</i><br />
			You are banned for one year. During this period you are not able to use the site and any communication with members of the community, or staff is forbidden. After the year, your membership will be reinstated, unless a forum administrator decides otherwise.</li>
	</ul>
	<br />
	The moderator and forum administrator’s decisions are final.
	<br />
	<br />
	We believe that this approach will ensure that people are dissuaded from breaking the rules, but give them a fair set of chances to redeem themselves. Whilst LB is not an open organisation, it strives to offer a democratic approach to its forums.
	<br />
	<br />
	To contact the moderation team, or the LB staff, please see <a href="../">here</a>.
